
[[Public Knowledge]] explains why Network Neutrality is so important.


URL = http://bricolab.com/2006/05/12/net-neutrality/

"The key issue of net neutrality, for those with slower internet connections, is that ISPs should not have the right to choke access to the content we access over the web. At the moment, we can choose where we surf, but if the big ISPs have their say, our ability to surf freely will be hampered by cut-off or drastically slowed down access to key services, thus directing us to ISP sponsored services instead."




